fault=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ X.\">X.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Cyr.\">Cyr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">5.4.28</biblScope></bibl>.—In early writers it rarely follows its case, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὑφηγητοῦ δ᾽ ἄ.</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0011.tlg007.perseus-grc1:502\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ S.\">S.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ OC\">OC</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">502</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὧν ἄ.</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0032.tlg007.perseus-grc1:6:1:14\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ X.\">X.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Cyr.\">Cyr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">6.1.14</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; freq. in later Prose, as always in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0086.tlg025.perseus-grc1:1071a:2\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Arist.\">Arist.</a></author>, <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Metaph.\">Metaph.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1071a2</biblScope></bibl>, al., cf. <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Plu.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.47c</biblScope></bibl>, etc. (Cf. Goth. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">inu,</tr_> OHG. <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ᾱνο</itype> 'without'; perh. akin to neg. pref. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἀ-.</foreign>)</sense> </entryFree>"}]}